4Works. DO NOT INSTALL ADAPTER WITHOUT SIM!
ByMcIvanon May 19, 2014
PRO TIP: DO NOT INSTALL THE ADAPTER WITHOUT A SIM! The sim contacts will catch on the open cavity and the sim tray will get stuck. It should REALLY say this on the package, I thought leaving the adapter in my phone would be a safe and easy storage spot. If you do this... Read below and use the strip to keep the sim contacts disengaged. I used the method below to save my phone!

IF YOU SIM TRAY DOES GET STUCK: Get the media devil packaging, the package has a "window" of clear thin plastic. Separate it from the envelope and cut a strip of this thin clear plastic slightly less than the width of your SIM tray. Gently slip this into the jammed tray, there will be 2-4 clicks/bumps, once fully inserted the sim tray will slide out. Do this on the side of the sim with the gold contacts, if you don't remember, keep trying both and wiggle the plastic deeper into the tray. With patience and careful force you can likely release all the sim leads/contacts that have jammed. DO NOT PULL FORCEFULLY. You will break things as other reviewers have done.

PRODUCT REVIEW: They're pretty nice, they are CNC machined so the fit is precise. I wish they had considered the above situation... Included a tool or a sim tray guard so the adapter could easily be stored with the phone. Anything this tiny is scary to store.

Most helpful critical review

11 of 14 people found the following review helpful
1Does not work with T-Mobile Micro SIM cards
ByKC "KC"on July 2, 2014
I bought this to adapt my brand new T-Mobile Micro SIM into a standard SIM slot. They even arrived on the same day.

The adapter is not the same size as a standard SIM card; it is very slightly wider. That fraction of a millimeter combined with the semi-flexible material meant I couldn't get sufficient traction with just my fingers to pull it back out. It took needle-nose pliers.

The Micro Sim card's fit into the adapter is not "snug." The semi-flexible adapter was too tight for the SIM card, and the adapter stretched and bowed outward away from the SIM card, until it inevitably lost grip on the card, and the card fell out.

I could get the "fit" to last for long enough to put the card in place, so I tried it anyway, and inserted it the same way you would with a standard SIM card, only more carefully. It did exactly what so many others have been complaining about (on this product and cheaper versions); it bent the metal connectors and left me with a useless phone.

I cannot recommend this product. In fact, since this is one of the highest rated of these adapters (which is why I bought this instead of the cheaper ones), I cannot recommend adapters at all.
